# Community Events Project: My Design Rationale

![community-events-sketch](community-events_sketch-iteration.jpg)

My design focuses on simplicity and usability for the user by implementing a familiar card-based set-up with event images, dates, attendees, and locations to attract the user's attention and help the users quickly scan through the events. The search bar at the top of the page improves how efficiently users can discover the events they like, and the category filters lets users personalize their view based on their preferences. The RSVP button of "Attending" makes the interaction intuitive and allows the user to show interest in an event with just one click. This button has a toggle function, making it easy for users to change their minds regarding an event and un-RSVP just as effortlessly. In addition, having a detailed modal view of each event (which includes the descriptions, price, and number of attendees) prevents overloading of information on the outside of the card while keeping essential details accessible inside of the card when the user clicks to view more details. The consistent padding, adequate whitespace, and black sans-serif font on a white background is to create a clean, modern look similar to popular platforms today, ensuring that the user feels comfortable when browsing through my page for a smoother, user-friendly experience.
